cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

The paper deals with unsupervised learning of visual similarities, which is a core problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel approach to similarity learning using deep learning and partial ordering, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of CNNs for representation learning, which is a common topic in cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on detailed pose estimation and object classification, which are applications of multimedia analysis and retrieval, falling under the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
